metadata.Plot: Gloria Swanson plays Tessie McGuire, a shopgirl who, when her boyfriend breaks their date one evening, goes to a party with a louche crowd of artists and hangers-on. She wows them with some zesty mimicry, and so gains an introduction to a better-paying job, impersonating a high-toned Russian countess to attract snobby customers into a dressmaker's establishment.
metadata.Writer: Frank Tuttle, Sidney R. Kent, Arthur Stringer
metadata.Actors: Gloria Swanson, Tom Moore, Lilyan Tashman
